        <h3>The Consolidated Division Logic: Decoding Final Science Marksheets</h3>
        <p>A frequent search regarding **bsc part 3 online marks 2024** is about the 'Final Scoring'. For the 2024 cycle, Indian Universities follow a strict science-policy threshold:</p>
        <ul style="margin-left: 20px;">
            <li><strong>Grand Aggregate</strong>: The final division (1st/2nd/3rd) is determined by the total marks obtained in Part 1, Part 2, and Part 3 (Theory + Practical). For Science, achieving 1st Division (60%) is a major benchmark for research recruitment.</li>
            <li><strong>Practical Pass Rule</strong>: A student must pass in the final-year practical exam separately. A failure in the 3rd-year lab work means the entire B.Sc result is listed as 'Fail (P)'.</li>
